The paper focuses on developing a brain-robot interaction system using EEG signals, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The proposed solution involves using deep learning techniques such as LSTM and attention mechanism, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). The system also involves controlling a robot, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). Finally, the paper discusses the practical application of the system in domestic services, which involves optimizing the system for energy-efficiency, a topic commonly discussed in machine learning (cs.LG).
